Distribution ( Fig. 5 ).
Parascolopsis akatamae
n. sp .
has been recorded based on specimens or identifiable photographs from southern Japan ( Akazaki 1984 ; Russell 1990 ; 2002;
Motomura et al . 2010
; this study), Taiwan (Hung et al . 2016; this study), Philippines ( Fujiwara 2017 ), Indonesia (
Shibukawa et al . 2003
;
White et al . 2013
; this study), Thailand (this study), India (Nalk et al . 2002;
Kannan et al . 2013
) and Iraq ( Jawad & Al-Badri 2014 ).

It is possible that
P. akatamae
is widely distributed in the Indo-West Pacific. The following records identified as “
Parascolopsis eriomma
” may actually be
P . akatamae
: South China Sea ( Randall & Lim 2000 ), Myanmar (
Psomadakis et al . 2020
), Timor and Arafura Seas (
Larson et al . 2013
), Arabian Sea ( Manilo & Bogorodsky 2003 ;
Psomadakis et al . 2015
), Red Sea ( Khalaf 2004 ; Golani & Fricke 2018 ) and Madagascar (
Fricke et al . 2018
).
